Something's been eating at me,

19:45.368 --> 19:46.258
and I got to find out
the answer.

19:46.411 --> 19:47.593
If Billy O'Donnell's alive,

19:47.745 --> 19:49.245
then who was the second body
in the coffin?

19:49.338 --> 19:50.688
We tried DNA testing. [laughs]

19:50.765 --> 19:53.024
I don't know why we didn't
do that in the first place.

19:53.251 --> 19:54.709
The second corpse was actually

19:54.711 --> 19:57.937
Springfield's beloved
business card printer

19:58.031 --> 19:59.438
Harold Baumgartner.

19:59.532 --> 20:02.200
He loved his wife so much,
he asked to be buried with her.

20:02.276 --> 20:03.592
Literally.

20:03.611 --> 20:06.186
Which also explains
all the other business cards

20:06.264 --> 20:07.205
we found in the coffin.

20:07.432 --> 20:09.615
This guy made
excellent business cards.

20:09.767 --> 20:11.600
40 years later, clear as a bell.

20:11.694 --> 20:14.361
So the blood type
was just a coincidence.

20:14.380 --> 20:16.772
[gasps]
Or maybe it was God's way

20:16.774 --> 20:20.109
of finding closure
for a bunch of lost souls.

20:20.127 --> 20:23.036
But that was some nice work
you did there, kid.

20:23.130 --> 20:25.372
Hey, how would you like
to join the force?

20:25.466 --> 20:27.541
I think she's too young, Chief.

20:27.635 --> 20:30.711
Lou, you can't know that
until you give her a gun.

20:30.730 --> 20:31.804
Am I right, Ralphie?

20:31.956 --> 20:34.139
Do I shoot toward the talking?

20:34.234 --> 20:36.792
I think I'm just gonna
run home now.

